    "Full sequences are used for updating, i.e., Monte-Carlo (MC) samples, instead of one-step update in Haarnoja et al. (2018), Christodoulou (2019).",
    "The reward signal R(a 1∶T) is given at the end of the episode, at time step T, and uses no discount, i.e., discount factor = 1 is utilized.",
    "This gives the following target for each soft Q-value update where y s T+1 = 0, and",
    "⋅|s T = 0 to keep the pre-trained high probabilities of stop tokens at certain states.",
    "This gives each action an equal contribution from the reward signal of the full sequence and an additional cumulative entropy term that favors actions where future states have high entropy."
